<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>lose one’s head • lose one’s mind</xh5><p> <i>lose one’s head—</i>1. lose one’s presence of mind; become confused: Don’t <u>lose your head</u> and start the car in gear. Take things quietly, put the lever in neutral.... 2. become emotionally attached to a person: She is at the age that she <u>loses her head</u> over every other boy she meets.</p><p> <i>lose one’s mind—</i>lose one’s mental faculties; go crazy: Robert <u>lost his mind</u> and was committed to an insane asylum.</p> </entry>
